soc.robot.sample3p

Class Sample3PClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • soc.baseclient.SOCDisplaylessPlayerClient
      • soc.robot.SOCRobotClient
        • soc.robot.sample3p.Sample3PClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SOCMessageDispatcher

    public class Sample3PClient
extends SOCRobotClient
    Sample of a trivially simple "third-party" subclass of SOCRobotClient using Sample3PBrain. See that brain class's javadoc for what's different from standard behavior. Also demonstrates how to tell the server this bot isn't programmed to handle seafarers scenarios (SOCFeatureSet.CLIENT_SCENARIO_VERSION): See buildClientFeats().
    Starting this bot as part of the Server:
    To have this bot run automatically as part of the server, start the server with command-line parameter -Djsettlers.bots.start3p=2,soc.robot.sample3p.Sample3PClient
    For details, see SOCServer.PROP_JSETTLERS_BOTS_START3P.
    Connecting to the Server:
    If this bot isn't started up as part of the SOCServer, it must know the server's robot cookie to connect:
    • Start the server with command-line parameter -Djsettlers.bots.showcookie=Y or a specific value like -Djsettlers.bots.cookie=bottest97481483
    • Start your bot client(s) with command line parameters like:
            localhost 8880 samplebot1 x bottest97481483
      localhost 8880 samplebot2 x bottest97481483
      localhost 8880 samplebot3 x bottest97481483
    Other Useful Server Properties:
    See /src/main/bin/jsserver.properties.sample comments for more details on any parameter.
    All server properties can be specified in a jsserver.properties file, or on the command line as -Dpropertyname=value.
    • To use third-party bots as a certain percentage of the bots in each game:
      jsettlers.bots.percent3p=50 (for 50%)
    • To give third-party bots more time before forcing their turn to end:
      jsettlers.bots.timeout.turn=18 (for 18 seconds). The default is SOCServer.ROBOT_FORCE_ENDTURN_SECONDS.
    • To wait before starting robot-only games at server startup:
      jsettlers.bots.botgames.wait_sec=30 (for 30 seconds)
      in order to give bot clients more time to connect first.
    Since:
    2.0.00
    Author:
    Jeremy D Monin
